OL,3,CCaribbean WW2 Dambusters veteran
OL,4,Ccelebrates 100th birthday
OL,6,FOne of Britain's last surviving West
OL,7,FIndian World War Two veterans has
OL,8,Fcelebrated his 100th birthday.
OL,10,FRalph Ottey was just 19 when he left
OL,11,FJamaica to join the RAF in 1944. He
OL,12,Flater transferred to RAF Woodhall Spa
OL,13,Fand served with the famous 617
OL,14,FSquadron.
OL,16,FMr Ottey, who now lives in in ,
OL,17,Fcelebrated his 100th birthday on
OL,18,FSaturday, 17 February, surrounded by
OL,19,Ffriends, family and fellow veterans.
